channel.description:
my jdk was messed up because one of the compilers from one of the sources i downloaded deleted some of the files from jdk... and it says i dont have jdk... but heres the prob: when i try to dl it says it IS installed and when i try to reinstall it it just comes back to the message "its already installed" and it wont reinstall or uninstall and i cant find the files at all on my computer which means I can't delete them!... therefore i cant compile...
HOW DO I FIX THIS

item.title: Z0mg JDK IS MESSED UP!?!?!?!?!
item.dc:creator: @Sideways_8 Sideways_8
item.description:
@Sideways_8 wrote:

Assuming your running Windows XP, and that it IS a problem with the JDK installation, click “start”, “My Computer”, on the left-hand side, click “Add or Remove Programs”, Scroll down to Java Development Kit X.X.X_XX and uninstall it, then reinstall JDK, if it still gives you a problem, their could be a problem with the JDK path in your compiler.
